<div id="review_3678599207" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3678599207" />
    <a title="Claire" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/121347271-claire"><img alt="Claire" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1636068757p2/121347271.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3678599207?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Claire" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Claire" href="/user/show/121347271-claire">Claire</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781595144867" href="/book/show/15812817-seizure">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3678599207&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3678599207" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6050280088828711815">DNF at 45%. 1.5 stars.<br/><br/>This is so disappointing!! I am so sad that I couldn’t enjoy this book more; the original plot was fantastic! I wish I had the tolerance for more teenage stupidity and ignorance.<br/><br/>When I first picked up Virals, I was expecting a hard-core sci-fi novel, not a mystery. It is important to find who killed Dr. Annoying! But...there was the swearing. And the plot. And the characters.<br/><br/>(By the way, this is partly a review for book one, so just a heads up! :) )<br/><br/>So Tory and her friends, </span>
  <span id="freeText6050280088828711815" style="display:none">DNF at 45%. 1.5 stars.<br /><br />This is so disappointing!! I am so sad that I couldn’t enjoy this book more; the original plot was fantastic! I wish I had the tolerance for more teenage stupidity and ignorance.<br /><br />When I first picked up Virals, I was expecting a hard-core sci-fi novel, not a mystery. It is important to find who killed Dr. Annoying! But...there was the swearing. And the plot. And the characters.<br /><br />(By the way, this is partly a review for book one, so just a heads up! :) )<br /><br />So Tory and her friends, all of whom are overly stereotypical, break into the lab where their parents work so they can *gasp* solve a mystery. Then they hear a poor lil puppy barking. Tory is angry that said puppy is being used for an experiment, so they steal the dog. Said dog is sick. Said dog was going to be euthanized because of this, but why not break the law? Why not interfere with some scientist’s experiment, illegally poach a puppy out of a lab, and then get infected with some dog virus?<br /><br />Rational, right?<br /><br />So then they get superpowers that give them dog instincts. This was actually my favorite part of the storyline! Still, I felt like the authors could have done so much more with this. Instead, they had these same four teenagers try to compete with adults in the solving of some murder mystery. Like I said, totally rational.<br /><br />And then the go on a big adventure, and then there was a HUGE plot twist at the end. Which blew me off my feet. <br /><br />So there was the happily ever after ending, and then in book 2 these teens with dog instincts go on another “rational” mission: find pirate treasure so they don’t have to move!!!<br /><br />Sorry. This is a very disorganized rant, but the main point that I have not mentioned yet is as follows:<br /><br />This was the plot of a children’s book. It had the same immature characters, but it was mixed in with WAY too much profanity, an overload of crude humor, and too many instances of teenagers trying to prove that their parents are dumb by breaking laws numerous times. For “good reasons”. It was not a pleasant read. Overall, I wouldn’t recommend this series to anyone. If the plot had been reworked into something enjoyable, these books could have been, in another world, some of my favorites.<br /><br />I’ll go read a book where the characters do irrational things for rational reasons now. See ya ;)</span>
  <a data-text-id="6050280088828711815" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
