<div id="review_1947012603" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1947012603" />
    <a title="Jenny" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34055121-jenny"><img alt="Jenny" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1947012603?book_show_action=true">Apr 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenny" href="/user/show/34055121-jenny">Jenny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781595144867" href="/book/show/15812817-seizure">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34055121-jenny?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34055121-jenny?shelf=age-ya">age-ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34055121-jenny?shelf=genre-mystery">genre-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1947012603" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15244607592895767395">3.5 ⭐️<br/><br/>Trigger warnings: violence, mentions of murder, description of dead bodies<br/>Content warning: biphobia, racism<br/><br/>Definitely not the best Virals novel, but still good.<br/><br/>The action in this second opus is a bit over the top. And when I say “a bit”, I kinda mean “a lot”... The whole pirate treasure thing is already a stretch, but the amount of people after them was way too much. Only counting the ones who seriously risked the Virals safety, that’s 5 people. And that doesn’t include other greedy people</span>
  <span id="freeText15244607592895767395" style="display:none">3.5 ⭐️<br /><br />Trigger warnings: violence, mentions of murder, description of dead bodies<br />Content warning: biphobia, racism<br /><br />Definitely not the best Virals novel, but still good.<br /><br />The action in this second opus is a bit over the top. And when I say “a bit”, I kinda mean “a lot”... The whole pirate treasure thing is already a stretch, but the amount of people after them was way too much. Only counting the ones who seriously risked the Virals safety, that’s 5 people. And that doesn’t include other greedy people connected to them. I feel like Reichs over complicated this story for the sake of having more to tell.<br /><br />Because in the end, this second novel just isn’t all that interesting. There were a few inconsistencies once again blurring the place this series hold in the Temperance Brennan world that could have easily been corrected in editing. <br /><br />I appreciated the development with Chance and the pack’s powers, which sets the atmosphere for the next books. Apart from that, it’s really not my favourite Virals book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15244607592895767395" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


